A reporter had to duck for cover during his live broadcast when a truck carrying millions of them overturned on Friday morning .
Jeff Dubois of KIRO , struggled to get through his report without swatting as the bees buzzed around Interstate 5 .
The cameraman Damien Glitch was stung more than 20 times .
The truck had just merged onto Interstate 5 around 3:30 a.m. .